BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: control_biosequence
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A Reporter associated with a BioSequence that has a context dependent predicted signal. e.g. a yeast reporter on a human array is a control_biosequence expected to be of low signal if no spikes are used. If spikes are used, the signal is expected to be high.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Host
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Organisms or organism parts used as a designed part of the culture (e.g., red blood cells, stromal cells).

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: QuantityUnitOther
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Quantity units not specified in MAGE.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: mm
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: millimeter, unit of distance

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: PopulationDensity
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The concentration range of the organism.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: CABRI_linenamesahc
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Database entry from CABRI, a database listing sources such as cell lines, bacteria, plasmids etc.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: change_light
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Change in light intensity or wavelength.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BibliographicReference
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A bibliographic reference is a published citation in a journal, book, other format e.g. web resource

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: diploid
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Describes a cell, nucleus or an organism with two copies of each chromosome.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Preservation
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Method and type of preserving the organism or biosource (i.e. keeping it in stasis).

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: antibody
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: glycoprotein of the immunoglobulin family that can combine specifically non-covalently, reversibly with a corresponding antigen

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: genetic_modification
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An action whereby an organism(s) has had genetic material removed, added, or rearranged.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: MTB_Database
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Database entry from the mouse tumor biology database, a resource for nomenclature of mouse tumors.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BioMaterialCharacteristicCategory
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: General descriptor of a BioMaterialCharacteristic category. Such as strain or line where the name of the strain or line is encoded in the FactorValue.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: pM
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: picomolar, concentration unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: http
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: uri for MGI mouse strain approved terms

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: DevelopmentalStageDatabase
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Database of developmental stage information.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BioSampleType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Used to tell when the BioSample is an extract or not.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: SoftwareType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Controlled terms that provide descriptors for the type of software.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ProtocolPackage
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The MAGE package for protocols.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: TumorGrading
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A descriptor used in cancer biology to describe abnormalities of tumor cells. E.g. an instance from NCI Thesaurus.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: DataType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Primitive data types found in computing languages such as float, boolean, etc.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ProtocolVariation
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The effects of different protocols or changes in protocols on experimental results are studied.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: http
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: uri for open galen

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: title
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Titles are names for documents but not for objects.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: cell_type
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A descriptor for FactorValue where CellType is compared.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ClinicalHistory
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The BioMaterial's (i.e., the patient's) medical record as background information relevant to the experiment.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ReplicateDescription
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: ReplicateDescription provides details about the type of replication used in the experiment.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: SoftwareVariation
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The effects of different software, software packages, or software versions on experimental results are studied.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: environmental_history_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An environmental history design type is where some aspect of the organism's environmental history is studied, such as exposure to teratogen, radiation, climate etc.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: family_history_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A family history design type is where the family history such as traits, characteristics, susceptibility to disease is studied

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: count
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Unit for a simple count of things

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: MESH
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: database entry from MESH, medical subject headings vocabulary resource

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ul
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: microliter, unit of volume

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: heavy_background
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The Zone is excluded due to smearing, streaking, or dense background in the Zone.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: linlog_normalization
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A transformation method in which low intensities are linearly scaled while high intensities are logarithmically scaled. The transition point is determined by minimizing the absolute deviation of the variance of log ratios.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: array_manufacture_software
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Software to control an arrayer.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: glass
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The array is made on a glass slide.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: short_oligo
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An element that is an oligonucleotide of less than 50 nucleotides in length (usually 20 to 25 nt as in Affymetrix probes).

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: unknown_experiment_design_type
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: ExperimentDesignType of unknown type.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: flip-dye_consistency
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A method of checking the consistency of expression levels between a pair of features from flip-dye hybridizations by studying the distribution of the logarithm of ratios of intensity ratios from the two spots.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Allele
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: One of two or more alternative forms of a gene or marker sequence and differing from other alleles at one or more mutational sites based on phenotype or sequence. Polymorphisms are included in this definition.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BAC
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: sequence from a bacterial artificial chromosome

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: SeqFeatureBasis
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Controlled terms for how the sequence features were determined (e.g., experimental, computational, etc.)

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: replicate_analysis
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A transformation method in which the intensity or ratio data from Features obtaining the same source DNA are combined. Analysis of the mean and standard deviation values for replicated Features can be used to exclude

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: JAX_mouse_strains
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Database entry from the resource at The Jackson Laboratory which has details of approved mouse strain nomenclature.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: alexa_546
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Absorbs at 556 nm, emission maxima at 573 nm (orange). Alexa dyes are have intense fluorescence, are photostable, stable over a wide range of pH, and are water soluble.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ArrayGroup
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An array group is a physical platform that contains one or more arrays that are separately addressable or a virtual grouping of arrays.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: TargetedCellType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The target cell type is the cell of primary interest. The biomaterial may be derived from a mixed population of cells although only one cell type is of interest.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: cell
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: One or more dissociated cell(s) possibly heterogeneous, excluding single cell organisms.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: peer_review_quality_control
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An experiment which has a peer reviewed publication attached.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: dye_swap_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An experiment design type where the label orientations are reversed.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: alexa_350
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Absorbs at 346 nm, emission maxima at 442 nm (blue). Alexa dyes are have intense fluorescence, are photostable, stable over a wide range of pH, and are water soluble.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: whole_organism
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: one or more of any unicellular or multicellular pro or eukaryote, including archaebacteria

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: liquid_handler_software
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Software used to control automated liquid handler.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: waterbath
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A device for controlling temperature by immersion in water.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: change_biomaterial_characteristics
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Indicates that one or more BioMaterialCharacteristics have changed during the treatment of a BioMaterial.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: hybridization
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The process of incubating one or more labeled extracts with an array.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: GALEN
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: database entry from GALEN common reference model, a resource for medical coding and terminology

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: cDNA_clone
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: sequence of complementary cDNA copy of an RNA molecule contained on a plasmid including the plasmid sequence, used when the entire clone is spotted non-exact synonym:cDNA, complementary DNA

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: 32P
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: 32 P, radioactive isotope of phosphorus used for labeling/detection purposes

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: consultant
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A contact who provides some service related to some aspect of the experiment which is not data coding or analysis. E.g. help with an experimental design.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Protocol
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Documentation of the set of steps taken in a procedure.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: GeographicLocationDatabase
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Database of geographic locations.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: linear_scale
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The scale is a standard base 10, non logarithmic scale.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: F+
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: mating type indicating the presence of F plasmid in a bacterial cell

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: agar
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A type of solid media commonly used for growing organisms

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: disease_state_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A disease state experiment design type is where the state of some disease such as infection, pathology, syndrome, etc is studied.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: individual_genetic_characteristic
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A descriptor for FactorValue where IndividualGeneticCharacteristic is compared.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: store
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The procedure of placing a physical object under specified conditions e.g. time, temperature, humidity, for the purposes of keeping it in the same state.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: irradiate
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: treatment of a biomaterial with radiation e.g. electromagnetic radiation

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: biosource_type
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: biosource type

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: plasmid
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: sequence from a plasmid, an extrachromosomal autonomously replicating piece of DNA excluding mitochondria and chloroplasts

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: consortium_member
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A member of a consortium of institutions.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: K
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Kelvin, unit of temperature

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: intravenous
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: delivery method whereby a compound or drug is administered via a vein

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: add
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The procedure of placing one physical object in the same container/physical space as another.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: text
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Text is a complete or excerpted document. Text is not a description provided by the user.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: PathogenTests
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Tests and results for pathogens infecting organism from which the biosource is derived

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: VolumeUnit
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Units used for volume measurements.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: arrayer
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An instrument capable of manufacturing arrays by spotting material.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: gram_percent
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: grams per deciliter, concentration unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: vortexer
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An instrument that mixes by rapid oscillation.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: PCR_questionable
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: PCR with multiple bands, or smear, in gel-separated reaction products

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: percent_vol/vol
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: percentage volume per volume, concentration unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: birth
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: the action of emergence and separation of offspring from the mother.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: polylysine
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A type of surface coating.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: mol
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: mole, unit of quantity

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: StrainOrLine
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Animals or plants that have a single ancestral breeding pair or parent as a result of brother x sister or parent x offspring matings.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Affymetrix_DAT
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A proprietary image data format that is lossless and containing one channel of data.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: biomaterial_provider
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A descriptor for FactorValue where BioSource providers are compared.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: GeographicLocation
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A descriptor of the location from which a BioMaterial was obtained, e.g. country, region, grid reference.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: oligo_synthesizer
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Hardware for synthesizing oligos.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: cells/ml
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: the number of cells per ml

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: RadiationUnit
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Units for measuring decay of a radioactive isotope over time.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Rem
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Roentgen Equivalent Man. Unit of dose equivalent, i.e., the measure of potential biological damage caused by exposure and absorption of radiation. Rem = absorbed dose (rad) x quality factor (Q). Q is unique to the type of incident radiation.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: synthetic_RNA
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: RNA which is generated by chemical or enzymatic (non cellular) means. E.g. T7 promotor generated RNA. Non-exact synonym: cRNA, complementary RNA

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Nutrients
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The food provided to the organism (e.g., chow, fertilizer, DEMM 10%FBS, etc.).

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: fractionate
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The action of separating a BioMaterial into one or more fractions e.g. differential centrifugation or FACS when used for cell sorting (see purify).

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: minutes
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: 60 seconds, unit of time

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ExperimentDesign
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: ExperimentDesign refers to both observational and experimental (perturbational) studies. The organizing principles of the study including the relationships between assays and the steps taken to interpret the data.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: EnvironmentalHistory
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A description of the conditions the organism has been exposed to that are not one of the variables under study.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: synthetic_DNA
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: DNA which is generated by chemical or enzymatic (non cellular) means.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: degrees_F
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: degrees Fahrenheit, unit of temperature

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: sex
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A descriptor for FactorValue where Sex is compared.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: non-targeted_transgenic_variation_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The modification of an organism due to the presence of DNA from another individual, e.g. of a different strain, species or breed. These do not include targeted transgenics such as knock-ins and knock-outs.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ExperimentDesignType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The ExperimentDesignType is the high level description for studies such as 'time series', 'dose response', etc.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: mix_by_inversion
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Mix through the process of inverting.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ConcentrationUnit
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Units used for concentration measurements.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: secreted_protein_identification_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A secreted protein identification design type identifies transcripts associated with a secretory pathway during translation and is used to infer which proteins are secreted or membrane bound.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: has_feature_shape
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Association of feature shapes to feature groups.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: User
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: User is a way to id a person in a database

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: chromosome
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Physical or theoretical sequence of, or representing a chromosome, one of the DNA molecules that comprises the genome.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: online_resource
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A publication type which is available online and which is not an online journal article, e.g. a web site or service.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: uM
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: micromolar, concentration unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Temperature
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The temperature that a biosource is exposed to.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: transcript_identification_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A transcript identification design type characterizes the length and position of transcripts and allows identification of all forms of transcripts in the genome.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ExperimentalFactor
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The factors in the study that are experimental parameters or regarded as influencing the experimental results.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: postmortem
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: biomaterial removed after the death of the organism

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: OrganismPartDatabase
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Database of organism part information.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BioAssay
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A bioassay is an abstract class representing physical and computational groupings of biomaterials and arrays.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: feces
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A biosource obtained as fecal matter.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: NormalizationDescription
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: NormalizationDescription provides details of the normalization strategy for the experiment.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: alexa_532
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Absorbs at 532 nm, emission maxima at 554 nm (yellow). Alexa dyes are have intense fluorescence, are photostable, stable over a wide range of pH, and are water soluble.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: investigator
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Person who contributed to the study.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: submitter
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Person who is the primary contact for data submitted to a database.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: PublicationType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Controlled terms for descriptors of the type of publication such as those used by Medline (review, book, etc.).

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: mix_general
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The procedure of agitating 2 or more materials in order to combine them. The materials may be of any state solid/liquid/gas.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Humidity
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The humidity that the biosource is exposed to.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: linear_regression_normalization
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A method of re-scaling intensity data from one channel relative to another based on regression of the intensities in one channel on those of the other. The slope of the regression line is used to re-scale the intensities in one channel for each Feature. This single parameter method assumes that there is a linear relationship between the intensities in one channel relative to the other.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Age
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The time period elapsed since an identifiable point in the life cycle of an organism. If a developmental stage is specified, the identifiable point would be the beginning of that stage. Otherwise the identifiable point must be specified such as planting.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: cm
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: centimeter, a unit of distance

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: control_spike_calibration
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A Reporter that could be hybridized to an exogenously added nucleic acid or protein (spike) before or during hybridization and is used as a control for data processing. It may be deposited at one or more known concentrations (calibration). A reporter may be a spike, a calibration control or both.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: http
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: uri for LOINC

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: nucleic_acid_extraction
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The procedure of extracting nucleic acid from the biomaterial.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: resuspend
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The procedure in which solid material is dispensed or dissolved in a liquid.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: species_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A species experiment design type assays differences between distinct species.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: cellular_modification_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A cellular modification design type is where a modification of the transcriptome, proteome (not genome) is made, for example RNAi, antibody targeting.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: funder
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Contact which provides funding for experiments.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: split
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The procedure of separating a BioMaterial into two or more BioMaterials of similar composition e.g. aliquoting a sample. The BioMaterial may be a BioSource (e.g., a tissue) or a BioSample (e.g, RNA extracted from a BioSource). Non exact Synonym:sample

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: male
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: individual whose sex organs contain only male gametes

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: MGEDOntology
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The MGED Ontology is a top level container for the MGEDCoreOntology and the MGEDExtendedOntology. The MGED ontology describes microarray experiments and is split into the MGEDCoreOntology, which supports MAGE-OM v1.0 and is organized consistently with MAGE, and the MGEDExtendedOntology, which expands MAGE v1.0 and contains concepts and relationships which are not included in MAGE.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: has_action
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Property of Treatment which indicates what action was performed.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: compound_based_treatment
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The treatment is effected by a defined chemical, biological or compound. The compound may be a drug, solvent, chemical, etc., with a property that can be measured such as concentration.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: SurfaceType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Controlled terms for descriptors for coating of the substrate.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: control_buffer
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A Reporter where only buffer was deposited on the array

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: binding_site_identification_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A binding site identification design type investigates protein binding sites on nucleic acids

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: PhysicalBioSequenceType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A physical biosequence type represents biological sequence that can be physically placed (spotted or synthesized) on an array e.g BAC, PAC.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: FactorValueSet
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A super grouping of FactorValueDependencies or FactorValues which describes combinations of conditions used to treat or describe a BioMaterial applied to a BioAssay, typically separating things on the basis of channels or the concepts of measured and reference samples e.g. 10% glucose, 1 hour AND 10mm NaCl, 2 hours in channel 1.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: PCR_primer_forward
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: single stranded oligo used for polymerase chain reaction

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: self_vs_self_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A self vs. self experiment design investigates variance and error estimates in the experimental system, and is where the same extract is compared.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: slice_analysis
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A method of analyzing the significant expression level of a Feature by calculating the intensity-dependent Z distribution value for the logarithm of the intensity ratios from the two channels.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: diameter_aberration
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The diameter of the Feature is much smaller or much larger than expected based on the spotting pin diameter.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: rectangular_feature
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The shape of the feature on the array is rectangular.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: has_cancer_site
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Property of disease state indicating the anatomical location(s) of disease.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: molecules
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: number of molecules, quantity unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: tumor_grading
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A descriptor used in cancer biology to describe abnormalities of tumor cells.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BioAssayDataCluster
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A grouping of bioassay data that has been organized by one or more mathematical functions into nodes.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: PreservationType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The type of method used to preserve (keep in stasis) the organism or biosource.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Measurement
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Measured values and units.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BioSourceProvider
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The resource (e.g, company, hospital, geographical location) used to obtain or purchase the biomaterial.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: accession
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: has accession number

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: concentrate
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Increasing the concentration of solutes in a solution or suspension.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Treatment
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A treatment is the process or action by which a biomaterial is created from an input biomaterial.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: pmol
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: picomoles, quantity unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: intron
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: sequence spliced out from a transcript

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: mtDNA
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: sequence from the mitochondrial genome

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: heating_block
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A device for controlling temperature.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: FamilyHistory
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Relevant aspects of genetic preconditions or family member's clinical history.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: TIFF
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Tag Image File Format (TIFF) is a common format to describe and store raster image data from scanners and other imaging devices. TIFFs may contain one or more channels and the data may be compressed using a lossless compression algorithm.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BarrierFacility
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Rating of containment system for the protection of organisms from infectious agents.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: oral_gavage
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: delivery method for drug or compound whereby the drug is administered via the mouth

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: TimeUnit
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Units used for time measurements.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: circadian_rhythm_design

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: clinical_information
