BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: TemperatureUnit
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Units used for temperature measurements.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: vacuum_dryer
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An instrument designed to remove excess liquid by vacuum and heating.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: PCR_fail
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: PCR where no products of any kind appear in gel-separated reaction products.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: organism_status
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The stage premortem or postmortem at which the sample was processed for extraction of biomaterials.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: FMA
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The Foundational Model of Anatomy (FMA) is concerned with the representation of concepts and relationships necessary for the symbolic modeling of the structure of the human body.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: has_image_format
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Association between physical bioassay and the format of images derived from the physical bioassay.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: mM
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: milimolar, concentration unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: growth_condition_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A growth condition experiment design type is where some part of the growth condition is changed for the purposes of the experiment, examples of growth conditions changed are media, temperature, humidity, light, nutrients.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: seconds
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: time unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: NormalizationDescriptionType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Controlled descriptors for the normalization strategy used for the experiment.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: operating_system
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Software upon which other software runs.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: PerturbationalDesign
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A perturbational design type is where the organism(s) are treated or manipulated or modified, for example a genetic modification, somatic modification

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: strain_or_line
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A descriptor of FactorValue where comparisons of strains or lines are made.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: MGEDExtendedOntology
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Location for those classes that are not in the Core ontology as they do are not containable in MAGE. It is not yet structured to work with the Core ontology

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: clinical_history_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A clinical history design type is where the organisms clinical history of diagnosis, treatments, e.g. vaccinations, surgery etc. is studied.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: cpm
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: counts per minute, unit of light emissions produced by ionizing radiation.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: IndividualGeneticCharacteristics
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The genotype of the individual organism from which the biomaterial was derived. Individual genetic characteristics include polymorphisms, disease alleles, and haplotypes.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: EST
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Sequence derived from expressed sequence tag. EST's are likely to be partial, single read and low quality sequences.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: frozen_storage
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Storage where the thing stored is stored below 0 degrees celsius.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: snRNA_gene
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: sequence from gene coding for small nuclear RNA

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: planting
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: time point at which a seed was planted

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: induced_mutation
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The modification of the genetic material (either coding or non-coding) of an organism by mutagenic compounds or irradiation.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: NodeValue
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Node values allow the organization of the nodes in relation to other nodes produced by mathematical functions such as a clustering algorithm.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: DerivedBioAssay
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A BioAssay that is created by the transformation of measured or derived BioAssays.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: months
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Unit of time corresponding to approx. one cycle of the moon's phases.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: preservation
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The type of protocol used to preserve (including storage or keep in statis) the biomaterial.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: control_unknown_type
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A Reporter indicated as being a control of unknown type.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: intergenic
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: sequence from the region between genes

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: RNA_stability_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A RNA stability experiment design type examines the stability and/or decay of RNA transcripts.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: disease_state
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A descriptor for FactorValue where DiseaseState is compared.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: subcutaneous
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Delivery method whereby a drug or compound is administered under the skin of the organism.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BioMaterialPackage
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Description of the source of the nucleic acid used to generate labeled material for the microarray experiment.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: has_factor_value_ontology_entry
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An association which links structured values for FactorValue.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: developmental_stage
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A descriptor for FactorValue where DevelopmentalStage is compared.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: paraffin_sample
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A biomaterial obtained embedded in paraffin (wax).

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: control_genomic_DNA
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A Reporter where genomic DNA has been deposited, the genomic DNA may be fragmented, e.g. salmon sperm DNA, Cot1DNA.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: eVOC
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Ontology of human terms that describe the sample source of human cDNA and SAGE libraries.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Media
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The physical state or matrix used to provide nutrients to the organism (e.g., liquid, agar, soil)

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Scale
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The scale (linear, log10, ln, etc) used to represent the value.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BioAssayDataPackage
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: MAGE package for BioAssayData.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: QualityControlDescription
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: QualityControlDescription provides details of the quality control aspects of the experiment.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ug
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: microgram, unit of mass

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: labeling
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The procedure of labeling a biosample.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: percent_confluence
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A measure of the density of an attached or monolayer culture (e.g., cell culture), e.g., 80 percent_confluence.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: aminosilane
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A type of surface coating.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: authors
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: has authors

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: displaced_feature_or_zone
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The Feature or Zone is displaced from its expected position, due to e.g. a bent spotting pin(s).

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: PCR_primer
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: single oligo used for polymerase chain reaction direction unspecified

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: aneuploid
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Describes a cell, nucleus or an organism whose chromosome number is not an exact multiple of the haploid number (n).

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: unknown_substrate_type
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: SubstrateType of unknown type.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: mRNA
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: sequence of a processed transcript capable of directing protein synthesis

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: HigherLevelAnalysisPackage
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: MAGE package for HigherLevelAnalysis

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ClinicalTreatment
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The current clinical treatment(s) of the patient from which the biosource is derived.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: percent_weight/vol
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: percent weight per volume, concentration unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: translational_bias_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A translational bias is an experiment design which characterizes the association of transcripts and translation machinery.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: has_description
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Direct named associations to Description in MAGE.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: nl
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: nanoliter unit of volume

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: WebRENI
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: database entry from WebReni A resource for rat and mouse unified nomenclature describing lesions

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: PCR
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Polymerase chain reaction. An element generated using this procedure.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Contact
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Organizations or individuals that may be contacted.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: CompoundDatabase
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Database of compound information.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ds_oligo
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: a double stranded oligonucleotide

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: compound_treatment_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A compound treatment design type is where the response to administration of a compound or chemical (including biological compounds such as hormones) is assayed.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: organellar_RNA
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: RNA obtained from an organelle, e.g., mitochondrion, ER, or chloroplast, excluding the nucleus.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Bedding
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Refers to the bedding material present in an animals housing.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: lowess_normalization
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Locally weighted linear regression of the intensities in one channel from a set of Features on those of the other channel. Lowess removes intensity-dependent dye-specific effects from the set of Features.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: square_feature
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The shape of the feature on the array is square.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: SubstrateType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Controlled terms for descriptors of types of array substrates.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Generations
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The number of cell passages if the organism or organism part that is cultured is unicellular or a cell culture otherwise the number of generations.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: R
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Roentgen. Unit of exposure to gamma or x-rays in the air. 1 R= 2.58E-4 coulombs per kg.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: mix_by_pipette
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Mix by drawing up and down with a pipette.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: half-life
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: t1/2. The period over which the activity or concentration of a specified chemical or element falls to half its original activity or concentration. Typically applied to the half-life of radioactive atoms but also applicable to any other situation where the population is of molecules of diminishing concentration or activity.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: http
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: uri for NCBI taxonomy database

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: gene
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: genomic sequence which corresponds to the primary transcript and uses the furthest 5' and 3' UTR's, doesn't include non transcribed regulatory regions. Can be experimentally or computationally determined

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: integer
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The values are integers.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: g/L
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: grams per liter, concentration unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: A
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Angstrom, unit of distance, 1 angstrom = 10 nanometers

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: GeneticModification
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The genetic modification introduced into the organism from which the biomaterial was derived. Examples of genetic variation include specification of a transgene or the gene knocked-out.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: consensus_DNA
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: DNA sequence produced from some base calling or alignment algorithm which uses multiple sequence as input

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: dilute
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Decreasing the concentration of solutes in a solution or suspension.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: mg/mL
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: milligrams per milliliter, concentration unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: spotted_protein_features
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: TechnologyType of FeatureGroup where protein (other than antibody) is spotted directly.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: mix_by_vortex
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Mix through the use of a vortexer.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: EMAP
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The Edinburgh Mouse Atlas Project (EMAP) ontology of mouse developmental anatomy covers the 26 developmental stages (Theiler Stages) from fertilization to birth.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: QuantitationTypePackage
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The MAGE package for defining classes for quantitation.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: laser_ablation_mark
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: mark made on slide using a laser which is used as a point of reference for orientation (fiducial)

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: replicate_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A replicate experimental design type is where a series of replicates are performed to evaluate reproducibility or as a pilot study to determine the appropriate number of replicates for a subsequent experiments.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: clone
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Sequence from some nucleic acid copy and the associated vector

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: http
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: uri for eVOC

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: not_extract
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The BioSample at any stage other than immediately before labeling.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: log_base_2
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The values presented are logarithm, base 2.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: has_maximum_measurement
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The maximum value in a range of measurements.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: beginning_of_stage
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: time point that indicates the start of some developmental stage

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BiologicalFactorCategory
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Factors that relate to properties of the biomaterial, its treatment, or its growth.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: PCR_primer_reverse
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: single stranded oligo used for polymerase chain reaction

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: agar_stab
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: agar stab, a cell culture inoculated into agar for long term storage

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: reverse_transcription
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Generation of a DNA strand from an RNA strand using reverse transcriptase.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BioAssayData
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: BioAssayData refers to the data files including images generated from one or more BioAssays.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: years
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: 365 days, time unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: fM
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: femtomolar, concentration unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: spike_quality_control
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An experiment in which spikes were introduced into some or all of the hybridizations for quality control or data transformation purposes.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: biopsy
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A biomaterial, usually tissue, cells, or fluid from a living organism

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: FiducialType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A descriptor that indicates the type of the fiducial such as chrome border of an Affymetrix array or a laser ablation mark.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: boolean
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The values are either TRUE or FALSE, which can be expressed as 0 and 1.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: MAD_stage
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: database entry from mouse anatomical dictionary for developmental stage term

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: time_series_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Groups of assays that are related as part of a time series.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: CellTypeDatabase
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Database of cell type information.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: AtomicAction
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An atomic action is a single step process on the biomaterial, e.g mix by inversion, wait, add

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: um
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: micrometer, unit of distance

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: co-expression_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A co-expression experiment design type identifies genes which are coordinately expressed and are potentially used to infer a role in a biological process(es)

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: biotin
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: a compound used for labeling/detection purposes

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ExperimentalFactorCategory
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A factor category describes factors which are under test in the experiment and allowable factor categories can be BioMaterialCharacteristics, Compound (names, concentrations) and Action etc. E.g. in an experiment where leukemia types are compared the factor categories are ALL and AML.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: not_uniform
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The source DNA for a Feature was not uniformly deposited.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: spin
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The procedure of applying a centrifugal force to a physical object.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: us
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: microsecond, unit of time

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: irregular_shape
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The perimeter of the spotted DNA on the slide is irregular.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: CellLineDatabase
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Database of cell line information.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: consensus_mRNA
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: mRNA sequence produced from some base calling or alignment algorithm which uses aligned or assembled multiple sequences as input.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: feature_extraction_software
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Software to create MeasuredBioAssayData from images.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: infect
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The organism (or organism part) has been exposed to a virus or pathogen.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ad_libitum
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A delivery method for compounds/drugs where the compound or drug is freely available.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: virus
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: one or more DNA or RNA based non cellular infective agent, including bacteriophage

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: genomic_DNA
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: high molecular weight DNA

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Unit
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Units of measure.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: OntologyEntry
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: External (to the MGED ontology) controlled vocabulary or ontology that can be referred such as ICD-9 or Gene Ontology.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: PhysicalArrayDesign
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Descriptions pertaining to the array.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: software_manufacturer
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Person or organization that manufactured the software.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: MassUnitOther
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Mass units not specified in MAGE.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ArrayPackage
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: MAGE package for describing the process by which arrays were manufactured.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: soil
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: soil, growth media for plants and other soil living organisms

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Roles
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Controlled terms for descriptors of the role of contact, e.g. submitter, biosource_provider.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ClinicalFindingDatabase
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Database of codes for clinical findings.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: NodeValueType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Controlled set of terms for describing the type of values (e.g., Euclidean distance).

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ConcentrationUnitOther
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Concentration units not specified in MAGE.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: missing_feature_or_zone
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The source DNA was not printed for a Feature or Zone on the slide, possibly due to lack of sample, broken or clogged spotting pin.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: unscaled
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The values are unordered and have no scale.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: jackknife_Pearson_correlation
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The jackknife Pearson correlation is the lowest Pearson correlation between two data series where one pair of values in the data series are omitted.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: http
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: uri for EMAP

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: remove
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The procedure of extracting/taking out a part of a reaction/contents of a container.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: book
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A publication type which has an ISBN.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ftp
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: uri of ICD9, international classification of diseases version 9

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: M
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: molarity, concentration unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: MassUnit
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Units used for mass measurements.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: is_expressed_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A design aimed at identifying genes expressed in biomaterials of interest.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Fiducial
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A marking on the surface of the array that can be used to identify the origin of the array.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: accession_version
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: has accession number version

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: biosequence_provider
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Provider of biosequences (clones, oligos etc) for deposition on the array.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: gene_knock_in
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The modification of an organism that inserts a functional gene at the site of a nonfunctional locus for that gene using recombinant methods.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: EnvironmentalStress
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Environmental stress is a treatment where some aspect of the environment is perturbed in order to stress the organism or culture, e.g. temperature shock, osmotic shock

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: category
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Category specifies a biological or a methodological factor.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: L
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: liter, unit of volume

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: unknown_surface_type
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A SurfaceType of unknown type.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: LightUnit
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Units for measuring the intensity of light.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ImageFormat
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Controlled terms for descriptors of the image file format (TIFF, JPEG, GIF, etc.)

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: DistanceUnit
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Units used for distance measurements.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: http
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: uri of NCI Thesaurus

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: age
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A descriptor for FactorValue where age is compared.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: DatabaseEntryType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Controlled set of descriptors for the type of database record such as a protein record (in SWISS-PROT) or a gene object (in SGD).

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ml
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: milliliter, volume unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: DerivedBioAssayType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Controlled set of descriptors for the type of derivation of the BioAssay such as averaging features, taking ratios of signal QuantitationTypes, and normalizing BioAssay data.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: string_datatype
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The values are a sequence of one or more characters.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: JPEG
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Joint Photographic Experts Group format, a common image data format containing grayscale or RGB data compressed with little to high data loss.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: fl
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: femtoliter, unit of volume

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Atmosphere
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The atmospheric conditions used to culture or grow an organism.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ms
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: millisecond, time unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: FeatureShape
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The expected shape of the feature on the array.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: MethodologicalFactorCategory
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The effects on results of changing protocols, hardware, software, or people performing the experiments are studied Examples are comparison of data across different labeling protocols, scanners, image quantification software, or laboratories.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: StrainOrLineDatabase
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Database of strain or line information.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: RNA
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Ribonucleic acid.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: blood
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A biomaterial obtained as fluid consisting of plasma, blood cells and platelets.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: mL/L
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: milliliters per liter, concentration unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: OrganismStatus
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The stage premortem or postmortem at which the sample was processed for extraction of biomaterials.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: pathogenicity_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A pathogenicity experiment design type is where an infective agent such as a bacterium, virus, protozoan, fungus etc. infects a host organism(s) and the infective agent is assayed.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BioMaterialCharacteristics
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Properties of the biomaterial before treated in any manner for the purposes of the experiment.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: purify
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The action of enriching a BioMaterial (organism, cell, nucleic acid etc) or Compound e.g. for FACS for positive selection or RNA cleanup the Action or ProtocolType is purify (see fractionate).

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Ci
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Curie. Unit of the rate of radioactive decay, i.e., the activity of that quantity of radioactive material in which the number of disintegrations per second is 3.7E10. 1 Ci = 3.75 x1010 atom disintegrations per second (dps).

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: exemplar_mRNA
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An exemplar is a representative cDNA sequence for each gene. The exemplar approach is a method that usually involves some initial clustering into gene groups and the subsequent selection of a representative from each gene group.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: premortem
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: sample which has been removed prior to the death of an organism

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: NCBI_taxonomy
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: identifier for a taxon provided by the NCBI taxonomy database

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: frozen_sample
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A biomaterial obtained frozen

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: bioassay_data_transformation_software
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Software used to transform the Measured or DerivedBioAssay data e.g. normalization.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: has_type
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Association to a controlled vocabulary for types.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Person
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The individual to contact regarding something provided such as a biomaterial.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: dye_swap_quality_control
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Indicates that a dye swap was performed for some or all hybridizations within an experiment

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: LabelCompound
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Compounds that are used for labeling extracts.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: TechnologyType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The technology type or platform of the reporters on the array.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: FactorValueDependency
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A group of FactorValues which refer to the same condition used to treat or describe a BioMaterial, e.g. 10% glucose, 1 hour OR larval stage, age 24 hours.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ControlType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Controlled terms for descriptors for the type of control design element.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BioAssayPackage
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: MAGE package for bioassay.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BioMolecularAnnotation
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: BioMolecularAnnotation experiment design types are those which are designed to investigate functions, processes, locations and identity at the molecular level e.g. binding site identification, genotyping.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: has_measurement
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A single measurement or the minimum value of a pair of values if a range is specified.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: unknown_sequence
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: BioSequence of unknown type

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: GeneticMaterial
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Genetic material may be DNA or RNA and identifiable as an entry in a public external database such as EMBL/DDBJ/GenBank or one of the model organism databases.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: organism_part_comparison_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An organism part comparison experiment design type compares tissues, regions, organs within or between organisms

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: wash_station
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An instrument designed to mechanically wash or stain arrays.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: genetic_modification_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A genetic modification design type is where an organism(s) has had genetic material removed, rearranged, mutagenized or added, such as knock out

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ctDNA
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: ctDNA: sequence from the chloroplast

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: DesignElementPackage
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The MAGE package for describing the elements located on the array.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: PolymerType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Controlled terms for descriptors of the type of polymer (RNA, DNA, protein) of the biosequence.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ZoneDefect
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A technical manufactured described defect for zones.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ProtocolType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A controlled set of terms to provide a descriptor for the type of protocol.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: image_acquisition_software
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Software to control a scanner and manipulate and save images.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Rad
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Radiation absorbed dose. Unit of energy absorbed per unit mass as a result of exposure to radiation. 1 rad = Absorption of 100 ergs per gram of material = 0.01Gy.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: cell_type_comparison_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A cell type comparison design experiment design type compares cells of different type for example different cell lines.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ReplicateDescriptionType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Controlled descriptors for the type of replication.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: http
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: uri for NIEHS database of controlled pathology terms

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: wash
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The process of applying a solvent (e.g. water) or a solution (e.g. SSC/SDS) to a BioMaterial or an array to remove impurities or unwanted compounds.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: liquid
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: media type, usually some sort of broth

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: DefectType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Defects associated with features or zones such as those that are missing or moved.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: hatching
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The point at which an organism emerges from an egg.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: DeliveryMethod
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Method used to deliver a compound for treatment.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: long_oligo
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An element that is an oligonucleotide of at least 50 nucleotides in length.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: feature_extraction
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The process of obtaining quantifiable values from the scanned image of the array.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: gene_knock_out
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The modification of an organism that renders a gene non-functional e.g. due to the removal of all, or part of, the gene using recombinant methods.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ChromosomalAberration
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An abnormality of a chromosome's number or structure, which excludes simple changes in sequence and is usually detectable by cytogentic and microscopic techniques such as FISH.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: polyploid
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Describes a cell, nucleus or organism with three or more copies of each chromosome.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Hardware
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The machine or instrument used.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: unknown_sex
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: organism(s) whose sex is unknown

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: spotted_ds_DNA_features
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A descriptor for the TechnologyType for a group of features where double stranded DNA is spotted on the array e.g. a PCR of a cDNA clone.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: alexa_633
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Absorbs at 632 nm, emission maxima at 647 nm (red). Alexa dyes are have intense fluorescence, are photostable, stable over a wide range of pH, and are water soluble.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BioSourceType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The form in which the Biosource is provided, may also be used to describe biosamples e.g. agar stab.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: clustering_software
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Software used to cluster the data.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: institution
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A contact's affiliation, e.g. university, research institute or business.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: http
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: uri for IUPAC_Clinical_Chemistry_Guidelines

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: predicted_gene
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: gene sequence which has been computationally predicted

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: YAC
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: sequence from yeast artificial chromosome

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: m
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: meter, distance unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: unknown_basis_feature
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Sequence feature whose derivation is unknown.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: chrome_border
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: the chrome border on an Affymetrix type array which is used as a point of reference for orientation (fiducial)

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Database
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Identifiable resource containing data or external ontologies or controlled vocabularies which has uniquely identifiable records.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: starvation
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Depriving an organism of food or nutrients

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: F-
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: mating type indicating the absence of F plasmid in a bacterial cell

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ORF
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: sequence which represents an open reading frame, a series of codon triplets deduced from a DNA sequence, that contain a start and a stop codon.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BiologicalProperty
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A biological property experiment design type is where an intrinsic characteristic of an organism(s) or biological system is examined.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BioSource
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The BioSource is the original source material before any treatment events.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: OperatorVariation
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The effects of different investigators, laboratories, or organizations on experimental results are studied.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: individual
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A descriptor for FactorValue where BioSources are compared.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: semisolid
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: semisolid media type

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: percent_weight/weight
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: percent weight per weight, concentration unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: centrifuge
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An instrument capable of applying centrifugal force to tubes or microtiter plates.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: log_base_e
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The values presented are logarithm, base e.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: organism_part
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The part of the organism's anatomy from which the biomaterial was derived, excludes cells. E.g. tissue, organ, system, or body location (arm).

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: 33P
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: 33 P, radioactive isotope of phosphorus, used for labeling/detection purposes.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: genotyping_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A genotyping experiment design type classifies an individual or group of individuals on the basis of alleles, haplotypes, SNP's.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: seed_dormancy
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: preservation type whereby the seed is maintained in a dormant state

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: HardwareVariation
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The effects of different hardware, types of hardware, or models of hardware on experimental results are studied.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: feeding
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Delivery method where a compound/drug is administered in food or water.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: http
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: uri for CellML

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: EpidemiologicalDesign
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An epidemiological experiment design type is where the biosource history is studied e.g. environmental, clinical and family history.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: description
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Free text that provides a brief summary. Description refers to objects and not documents.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Parameter
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A parameter is a variable within a protocol.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: DiseaseStateDatabase
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Database of disease state information.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: TheoreticalBioSequenceType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A theoretical biosequence type is an abstraction used for annotation design of elements, e.g. gene, intron.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Spearmans_rank_correlation
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Computed as the ordinary Pearson correlation coefficient between two groups of rankings.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: nitrocellulose
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The array is made on a nitrocellulose filter.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: hermaphrodite
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: an organism with both male and female sexual organs in one individual

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: SomaticModification
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The organism has had non-genetic parts removed, added, or rearranged.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: has_property_set
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: These are associations to MAGE property sets, specifying NameValueType. These are used to add additional structure to MAGE where the model is insufficient.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: DevelopmentalStage
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The developmental stage of the organism's life cycle during which the biomaterial was extracted.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: development_or_differentiation_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A development or differentiation experiment design type assays events associated with development or differentiation or moving through a life cycle. Development applies to organism(s) acquiring a mature state, and differentiation applies to cells acquiring specialized functions.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BioSequenceType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Controlled terms for descriptors indicating the type of biosequence. Types may be physical (e.g BAC, cDNA clone), or computational (e.g unigene cluster, consensus)

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: http
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: uri for MESH

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: experimental_and_computational_feature
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Sequence features derived by both computational and experimental methods.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: disease_staging
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The stage or progression of a disease in an organism. Includes pathological staging of cancers and other disease progression.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: TargetedCellTypeDatabase
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Database of targeted cell type information.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: pl
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: picoliter, volume unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: iterative_mean_log_centering
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A method of re-scaling ratio data by subtracting the mean log base 2 ratio from each log2(ratio). This adjusts the mean log2(ratio) to zero.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: mating_type_a
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Mating type of S. cerevisiae.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: order
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Chronological order in which treatment occurred in relation to other treatments. More than one treatment can have the same chronological order indicating that they happened simultaneously.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: http
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: uri for The Foundational Model of Anatomy (FMA)

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BioSequencePackage
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: MAGE package for biological sequences (biosequence).

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: http
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: uri for Mouse Tumor Biology Database

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: cfu/ml
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: the number of colony forming units per ml

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: biomaterial_purity
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: purity of biomaterial

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Individual
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Identifier or name of the individual organism from which the biomaterial was derived.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: is_contaminated
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The clone used to originate the BioSequence which corresponds to the reporter was found to be contaminated (e.g. well-well contamination) on examination.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: hybridization_chamber
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A chamber in which the hybridization is performed which maintains constant conditions.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: HUMAT
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Ontology of human developmental anatomy for Carnegie stages 1-20.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: WarningType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Controlled terms for descriptors of the warnings associated with reporters.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: cell_line
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A descriptor for FactorValue where CellLine is compared.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: computer
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A device capable of applying software.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: molecular_mixture
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: an unspecified collection of heterogeneous molecules, e.g. lipids, carbohydrate , nucleic acids and proteins

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: mixed_sex
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A population of multiple sexes, e.g. a mixture of females and males, or males and hermaphrodites.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: experimental_feature
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An experimentally defined sequence feature.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Haplotype
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The genotype of a single chromosome (i.e., the haploid genotype) that is known and relevant to the experiment being performed.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: nuclear_RNA
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: RNA obtained from the nucleus.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: nm
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: nanometer distance unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: kg
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: kilogram, 1000 grams, unit of mass

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: silicon
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: the array is made on silicon

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: DesignElementGroupType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Controlled set of descriptors for indicating the specific type of a Feature, Reporter, or CompositeSequence.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: control_label
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Reporter used as a control where some label has been deposited. This includes fluor and radioactively labeled oligos and fluors alone.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: hours
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: 60 minutes, time unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Light
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The photoperiod and type (e.g., natural, restricted wavelength) of light exposure.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: spotted_antibody_features
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: TechnologyType of FeatureGroup where antibodies are spotted directly.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: HardwareType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Controlled terms for descriptors of types of hardware.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: CellType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: CellType, the type of cell used in the experiment if non mixed, if mixed the TargetedCellType should be used, example of instances, epithelial, glial etc.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: quality_control_testing_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A quality control testing experiment design type is where some aspect of the experiment is quality controlled for the purposes of quality assurance

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: genetic_variation
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A descriptor for FactorValue where GeneticVariation is compared.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: AuditAndSecurityPackage
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: MAGE package for contacts including organizations and people.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: operon_identification_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An operon identification experiment type is designed to identify locations and members of operons in a genome.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ratio_statistics_normalization
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A method of re-scaling intensity data from one channel relative to another based on an iterative method of calculating single parameter linear normalization factors. This method allows calculation of confidence intervals for the data set.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: strain_or_line_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A strain or line experiment design type assays differences between multiple strains, cultivars, serovars, isolates, lines from organisms of a single species.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Software
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The software application used.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: CellLine
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The identifier for the cell line if one was used as a biomaterial.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: g
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: gram, unit of mass

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: organism
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: one or more of any unicellular or multicellular pro or eukaryote, including archaebacteria

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ExperimentPackage
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The descriptions associated with the Experiment package of MAGE

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: QuantitationType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The QuantitationType provides a method for calculating a single datum of the BioAssayData matrix.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: linear_amplification
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Amplification of nucleic acid sequence by making many copies off the same template. An example is the use of the T7 promoter for amplification by transcribing many RNA copies.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: nmol
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: nanomoles, quantity unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: http
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: uri for the ChemIDplus database

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: decontaminate
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Treatment to remove organisms present that were not planned as part of the study (e.g., mycoplasma).

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: individual_genetic_characteristics_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An experiment design type where genotype, haplotype, or other individual genetic characteristics are compared.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: intramuscular_injection
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Delivery method for a compound or drug where the substance is administered via an injection into the muscle.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: QuantityUnit
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Units used for quantity measurements.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Euclidean_distance
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The Euclidian distance is the square root of the sums of the differences between the squares of each pair of values in a data series.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: has_family_relationship
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The family relationship relative to the patient. E.g. brother or father.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: MaterialType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Controlled terms for the state of the BioMaterial. Each state (BioSource, different BioSamples, and LabeledExtract) have MaterialTypes. Examples are population of an organism, organism, organism part, cell, etc.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: cosmid
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: sequence from cosmid, a hybrid cloning vector containing cos sites, usually of ~40kB size

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: intraperitoneal_injection
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A delivery method for compound or drug whereby the substance is administered via the peritoneum.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: spotted_colony_features
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: TechnologyType of FeatureGroup where bacterial or other colonies are spotted directly.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: PAC
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: sequence from a P1 artificial chromosome

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: DiseaseState
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The name of the pathology diagnosed in the organism from which the biomaterial was derived. The disease state is normal if no disease has been diagnosed.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: computational_feature
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Computationally derived sequence feature.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: DesignElementGroup
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A DesignElementGroup holds information on Features, Reporters, or CompositeSequences.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: alexa_660
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Absorbs at 663 nm, emission maxima at 690 nm (far-red). Alexa dyes are have intense fluorescence, are photostable, stable over a wide range of pH, and are water soluble.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: hybridization_station
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An instrument which controls hybridization conditions, into which a hybridization chamber may fit.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: PCR_amplification
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Amplification of nucleic acid sequence by use of the polymerase chain reaction whereby the number of templates grows geometrically with each cycle.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Compound
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A drug, solvent, chemical, etc., with a property that can be measured such as concentration.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Pearson_correlation
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The Pearson correlation is defined as the covariance of two data series divided by the product of their standard deviations.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Adult_Mouse_Anatomy
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: This ontology describes the anatomy of the adult mouse. It contains anatomical structures for the postnatal mouse (Theiler stage 28).

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: DNA
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Deoxyribonucleic acid.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: polyA_RNA
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: RNA which has been obtained by selection for polyA tracts. Exact synonym:polyA+_RNA

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Water
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Water consumed by or enveloping the organism that the biosource is derived from.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: weeks
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: 7 days, unit of time

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Action
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Procedures used during treatment.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: control_reporter_size
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A Reporter of whose BioSequence is of known length used as a methodological control for hybridization efficiency.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: MGEDCoreOntology
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An ontology developed by the Microarray Gene Expression Data (MGED) Society to provide descriptors required for MAGE v.1 documents.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: array_manufacturer
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Person or organization that manufactured the array.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: homogenizer
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An instrument which fragments tissues or other biomaterials.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: FamilyMember
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Member of the biosource's family.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: has_genetic_material
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Association of genetic material to genetic modification to indicate the target of modification.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: dl
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: deciliter, unit of volume

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: nylon
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The array is made on a nylon membrane.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: degrees_C
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: degrees celsius, unit of temperature

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: URI
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Uniform Resource Identifier

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: vector
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Sequence from a vector, DNA of any transmissible agent e.g. plasmid or virus into which a segment of foreign DNA can be spliced, does not include insert sequence. These terms should be used when other terms such as plasmid, YAC, BAC are used.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Phenotype
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Phenotype and traits not including pathology and disease.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: set_temperature
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An action where the temperature is specified.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: alexa_488
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Absorbs at 495 nm, emission maxima at 519 nm (green). Alexa dyes are have intense fluorescence, are photostable, stable over a wide range of pH, and are water soluble.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: HistoryFactor
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Factors that are measured or observed parts of the study but not induced or under the control of the experiment. These factors do not have protocols (e.g., epidemiology factors).

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ng
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: nanogram, a mass unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: specified_biomaterial_action
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Conceptual action for specified protocol applied in treatment.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: promoter
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: genomic sequence 5' to a gene where the transcription initiation complex forms.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: PCR_amplicon
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: BioSequence generated by means of polymerase chain reaction

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: mg
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: milligram, mass unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: transcript
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: sequence that represents the product of an RNA polymerase engaged in transcription

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: PhysicalBioAssay
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A physical bioassay is the combination of arrays and biomaterials as in a hybridization.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: physical_characteristics
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A descriptor for FactorValue where PhysicalCharacteristics are compared.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ArrayDesignPackage
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: MAGE package that describes the array layout and design. The array may be physical or virtual.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: eclosion
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Emergence of an adult insect from its pupa or cocoon.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: DNA_sequencer
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An instrument that produces DNA sequences.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: normalization_testing_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A normalization testing experiment design tests different normalization procedures.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: CellML
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Ontology describing anatomical and physiological relationships.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: optimization_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An optimization experiment design type is where different protocols or protocol parameters are compared.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Organization
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The organization (e.g, company, hospital) to contact to obtain or purchase something.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: MeasurementPackage
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: MAGE package for measurement.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BioMaterial
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Description of the processing state of the biomaterial for use in the microarray hybridization.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: address
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: has postal address

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: hardware_manufacturer
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Person or organization that manufactured the hardware.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: operator_variation_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An operator variation experiment design type assesses the operator performance and relation to data consistency and quality.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: FamilyRelationship
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The family relationship relative to the patient. E.g. brother or father.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: cell_lysate
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: cell lysate, a collection of cells whose membranes have been disrupted

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: x(times)
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: multiple of stock solution concentration, concentration unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: unknown_protocol_type
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: ProtocolType of unknown type.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: DesignElement
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Design elements are reporters, features, and composite elements as defined by MAGE.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: not_sequence_verified
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The sequence of the BioSequence that relates to this reporter has not been sequence verified by the experimenter.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: alexa_594
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Absorbs at 590 nm, emission maxima at 617 nm (red). Alexa dyes are have intense fluorescence, are photostable, stable over a wide range of pH, and are water soluble.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: OrganismDatabase
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Database of taxonomic information.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: alexa_430
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Absorbs at 433 nm, emission maxima at 539 nm (yellow-green), Alexa dyes are have intense fluorescence, are photostable, stable over a wide range of pH, and are water soluble.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: image_acquisition
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The process of generating an image from the array.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ClinicalFinding
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Clinical findings that are distinct from the disease state and can be referred to from an established controlled vocabulary or ontology. An example might be a test performed and/or finding.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: DiseaseStaging
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The stage or progression of a disease in an organism. Includes pathological staging of cancers and other disease progression.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: uncentered_Pearson_correlation
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The uncentered Pearson correlation is defined as the Pearson correlation for two data series where the mean of each data series is assumed to be zero.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: pfu/ml
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: the number of plaque forming units per ml

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: spectrophotometer
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Hardware for measuring light at different wavelengths.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: behavioral_stimulus
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The organism is forced to respond to a stimulus with some behavior (e.g., avoidance, obtaining a reward, etc.)

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: journal_article
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A article published in a print or online journal having an ISSN.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: hardware_variation_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A hardware variation experiment design type compares different types of hardware for performance, reproducibility, accuracy and precision.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Cy5
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: flurophore used for labeling/detection purposes

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: LOINC
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Database resource for universal identifiers for laboratory and other clinical observations

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: data_coder
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Person who codes data.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: sex_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A sex experiment design type assays differences associated with an organism's sex, gender or mating type.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: DescriptionPackage
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: MAGE package for description of annotations and references to annotations.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: FlyBase
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: curated database containing information on Drosophila genes, alleles etc

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: clinical_treatment
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A descriptor for a clinical treatment for a patient.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: total_intensity_normalization
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A method of re-scaling intensity data from one channel relative to another based on the ratio of the sums of the fluorescent intensities from each channel for all Features: N = sum(Ri) / sum(Gi) . The ratio is used to re-scale the intensities in one channel for each Feature. This is a single parameter linear normalization method.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ellipsoid_feature
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The shape of the feature on the array is circular or oval.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: cc
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: a cubic centimeter, volume unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: bioassay_data_transformation
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A computational procedure used to process or transform one BioAssayDataCube into another.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: dose_response_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A dose response design type examines the relationship between the size of the administered dose and the extent of the response of the organism(s).

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: control_empty
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A Reporter where no material or buffer was deposited on the array

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: LabeledExtract
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The BioSample after labeling for detection of the nucleic acids.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: protein
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Polymer of amino acids.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: extract
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The BioSample immediately before labeling.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: change_humidity
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The action of changing the relative humidity, e.g. from 1% to 10%.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: log_base_10
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The values presented are logarithm, base 10.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: loop_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A loop experiment design is where labeled extracts are compared in consecutive pairs.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: operon
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: sequence which represents an operon, a unit of genetically linked genes displaying coordinated and regulated gene activity, originally described in prokaryotes

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Organism
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The genus and species (and subspecies) of the organism from which the biomaterial is derived from.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: QualityControlDescriptionType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Controlled descriptors for the quality control strategy for an experiment.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: umol
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: micromoles, quantity unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: liquid_handler
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Hardware for automated liquid transfer and handling.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: curator
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Person who curates data.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: spotted_ss_oligo_features
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The TechnologyType of the FeatureGroup is spotted single stranded oligonucleotides (of any length) on the substrate.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: dissect
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The action of removing one or more OrganismParts.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: injury_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An injury experiment design type is where the response of an organism(s) to injury or damage is studied.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: TDMS
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Toxicology Data Management System, a database resource for systems, organs, pathology, etc.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: OtherUnit
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Other units are those types not specified in MAGE such as lumens, radioactivity, etc.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: pool
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The process of combining two or more BioMaterials.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: array_manufacturing
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The process of manufacturing the array.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: FactorValue
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The value of an ExperimentFactor.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: PNG
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Portable Network Graphic, a lossless image data format.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: FeatureDefect
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A technical manufacturer described defect for features.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Ploidy
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The number of single sets of chromosomes in the cell or an organism e.g., haploid, diploid, triploid, etc.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Histology
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Microscopic morphology of tissues.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: total_RNA
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Total cellular and nuclear RNA.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: GrowthCondition
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A description of the conditions used to grow organisms or parts of the organism. This includes isolated environments such as cultures and open environments such as field studies.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: organellar_DNA
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: DNA from organelles such as the mitochondria or chloroplast.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: in_situ_oligo_features
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The TechnologyType of the FeatureGroup is manufactured using in situ methods such as photolithography (e.g. Affymetrix) or chemical synthesis (e.g. Agilent)

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: fmol
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: femtomole, unit of quantity

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: reference_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A reference experiment design type is where all samples are compared to a common reference.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: change_temperature
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Change in temperature.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: array_scanner
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An instrument capable of acquiring images of arrays.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: thermal_cycler
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An instrument designed to automatically raise and lower the temperature of wells or tubes. Usually used to perform PCR.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: TimeUnitOther
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Time units not specified in MAGE.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: software_variation_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A software variation design type compares different types of software for performance, accuracy, precision and reproducibility.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: http
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: uri for cabri, common access to biological resources and information

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Reporter
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Description of the material placed on a feature (spot).

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ss_oligo
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: sequence of a single stranded synthesized oligonucleotide

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: data_analyst
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A contact who performs data analysis, e.g. statistician.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: http
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: uri for RENI

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: cell_cycle_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A cell cycle design experiment design type is one that assays events that occurs in relation to the cell cycle, which is the period between the formation of a cell, by division of its mother cell and the time when the cell itself divides to form two daughter cells.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: all_pairs
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An all pairs experiment design type is where all labeled extracts are compared to every other labeled extract.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: alexa_568
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Absorbs at 556 nm, emission maxima at 573 nm (orange). Alexa dyes are have intense fluorescence, are photostable, stable over a wide range of pH, and are water soluble.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: stimulus_or_stress_design
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A stimulus or stress experiment design type is where the response of an organism(s) to the stress or stimulus is studied, e.g. osmotic stress, heat shock, radiation exposure, behavioral treatment etc.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ComplexAction
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Complex actions are composed of multiple steps (as opposed to AtomicAction) e.g. mRNA labeling, protein purification.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: days
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: 24 hours, time unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: DiseaseLocation
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Anatomical location(s) of disease.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: IUPAC_Clinical_Chemistry_Guidelines
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A resource of vocabularies for describing clinical tests, e.g. blood chemistry.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: dpm
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: disintegrations per minute, unit of atom disintegrations per minute. dpm = (cpm - measured background)/efficiency. Efficiency is dependent on the radioisotope used and the instrument.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: haploid
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Describes a cell, nucleus or an organism with one copy of each chromosome.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Transformation
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The process by which BioAssays (data, elements, quantitation types) are averaged normalized, selected, filtered, or otherwise changed into a new set of BioAssay data.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: FailType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Controlled terms for descriptors of failures (as in PCR) associated with reporters.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ICD-9-CM
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Database entry from ICD 9 2001, international classification of diseases 9, clinical modification 2001.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: incubate
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The procedure of placing a physical object under specified conditions e.g. time, temperature, humidity for the purposes of obtaining a different product.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: low_intensity_filter
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A transformation method that involves removal of Features with low intensities in one or both channels from the data set. The threshold for exclusion is usually based on some estimation of local background intensity.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BioSequence
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A representation of a DNA, RNA, or protein sequence.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: UMLS
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Database resource, unified medical language system, an ontology constructed by merging several disparate ontologies, available from NIH.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: CBIL_CV
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: a controlled vocabulary provided by CBIL

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: value
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Property indicating that there is a class has a value which has some uncontrolled value.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: female
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: of, pertaining to, or designating the sex that only produces gametes that can be fertilized by male gametes.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: grow
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A ComplexAction or ProtocolType describing growth of an organism or cell culture.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: amol
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: attomole, quantity unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: coitus
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: sexual intercourse or copulation

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: FeatureGroup
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Technology-based grouping of features representing individual locations on the array.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: gene_fragment
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: sequence of part of a gene, which is missing one or both ends

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: exon
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: sequence which represents regions of a transcript that are joined to another exon during splicing

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: float
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The values are floating point numbers, arbitrary precision.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: http
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: uri for CBIL anatomy terms

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: place
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The procedure of putting a physical object in a container/physical space.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Experiment
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The complete set of bioassays (hybridizations) and their descriptions performed as an experiment for a common purpose. Here we take experiment to mean an observational or perturbing study. An experiment will be often equivalent to a publication.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: DistanceUnitOther
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Distance units not specified in MAGE.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: InitialTimePoint
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The point from which measurements of age were taken.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: cytoplasmic_RNA
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: RNA obtained from the cytoplasm.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Sex
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Term applied to any organism able to undergo sexual reproduction in order to differentiate the individuals or types involved. Sexual reproduction is defined as the ability to exchange genetic material with the potential of recombinant progeny.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: GIF
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Graphics Interchange Format , a common image data format containing RGB data compressed with fairly high data loss.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ProtocolParameterType
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Descriptors for protocol parameter types, e.g. compound concentration, media type.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: pg
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: picogram, mass unit

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: BioSample
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The BioSource after any treatment.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: wait
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Allow time to pass. It's measurement should be a unit of time.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: has_fiducials
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Association to fiducial for array group.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: fg
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: femtogram, unit of mass

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: tRNA gene
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: sequence from a gene coding for transfer RNA

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: polypeptide
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: sequence of a protein, a linear amino acid polymer

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: transfect
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The process of bringing about genetic alteration of any cell or organism by a variety of means including recombinant DNA technology, viruses, chemical mutagens, and X-rays.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ChemID
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Database entry from the ChemIDplus database which stores information on the structure, identifiers etc for compounds.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ChromosomalAberrationDatabase
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Database of chromosomal aberrations.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Genotype
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The total sum of the genetic information of an organism that is known and relevant to the experiment being performed.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Cy3
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: flurophore used for labeling/detection purposes

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: http
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: uri for mouse anatomical dictionary for the adult mouse

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: technical_replicate
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A replicate where the same BioSample is use e.g. the same pool of RNA used to assess technical (as opposed to biological) variation within an experiment.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: alexa_680
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Absorbs at 679 nm, emission maxima at 702 nm (far-red). Alexa dyes are have intense fluorescence, are photostable, stable over a wide range of pH, and are water soluble.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: biological_replicate
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A replicate that consists of independent biological replicates made from different individual BioSources.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: http
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: uri for jax mouse gene indices

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: rRNA gene
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: sequence from gene coding for ribosomal RNA exact synonym:ribosomal RNA gene

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: VolumeUnitOther
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Volume units not specified in MAGE.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: Node
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A node is an individual component of BioAssayDataCluster that groups design elements, quantitation types, and BioAssays together. A node may contain other nodes.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: OrganismPart
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: The part of the organism's anatomy from which the biomaterial was derived, excludes cells. E.g. tissue, organ, system, or body location (arm).

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: MethodologicalDesign
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: A methodological experiment design type investigates differences caused by application of protocols, hardware, software and bioassay relationships, e.g quality control, replicates, loop.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: mating_type_alpha
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: Mating type of S. cerevisiae.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: http
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: uri for HUMAT

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: sonicator
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: An instrument for sonicating biomaterials.

BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.name: ftp
BL_MGEDOntologyTerm.definition: uri for flybase

BL_OntologyTermType.name: Individual
BL_OntologyTermType.description: An individual is an instance of one or more classes.

BL_OntologyTermType.name: Class
BL_OntologyTermType.description: A class represents a concept and is a set with multiple inheritance and properties.

BL_OntologyTermType.name: DatatypeProperty
BL_OntologyTermType.description: A property that relates objects to datatype values.

BL_OntologyTermType.name: ObjectProperty
BL_OntologyTermType.description: A property that relates objects to other objects.

BL_OntologyTermType.name: TransitiveProperty
BL_OntologyTermType.description: A property that is transitive. A TransitiveProperty is a subclass of ObjectProperty.

BL_OntologyTermType.name: UnambiguousProperty
BL_OntologyTermType.description: A property that an instance y can only be the value of a Property P for a single instance x.

BL_OntologyTermType.name: UniqueProperty
BL_OntologyTermType.description: A property that can only have one (unique) value y for each instance x.
